  Item 3.03Material Modification to Rights    
  of Security Holders.Upon issuance of the    
  Series Y Preferred Stock (as defined in     
  Item 5.03 below), the ability of The        
  Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (the              
  “Registrant”) to declare or pay dividends   
  on, or purchase, redeem or otherwise        
  acquire, shares of its common stock will    
  be subject to certain restrictions in the   
  event that the Registrant fails to pay      
  dividends on its Series Y Preferred Stock.  
  These restrictions are set forth in the     
  Certificate of Designations establishing    
  the terms of the Series Y Preferred Stock,  
  a copy of which is listed as Exhibit 3.1    
  to this Report on Form8-Kand is             
  incorporated herein by reference.Item       
  5.03Amendments to Articles of               
  Incorporation or Bylaws; Change in Fiscal   
  Year.On September 23, 2024, the Registrant  
  filed a Certificate of Designations to its  
  Restated Certificate of Incorporation with  
  the Secretary of State of the State of      
  Delaware setting forth the terms of its     
  6.125% Fixed-Rate Reset Non-Cumulative      
  Preferred Stock, Series Y, liquidation      
  preference $25,000 per share (the “Series   
  Y Preferred Stock”). A copy of the          
  Certificate of Designations relating to     
  the Series Y Preferred Stock is listed as   
  Exhibit 3.1 to this Report on Form8-Kand    
  is incorporated herein by                   
  reference.Additional exhibits are filed     
  herewith in connection with the offering,   
  issuance and sale of depositary shares      
  representing interests in the Registrant’s  
  Series Y Preferred Stock under the          
  Registrant’s Registration Statement on      
  FormS-3(FileNo. 333-269296).
